               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Ṣalota kidān za-nagh "Morning Prayer of the Covenant" (fols. 2ra – 8ra, l.7)&#xD;
II) Anaphoras (fols. 8ra – 22va, 91ra – 124va)&#xD;
II-1) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 8ra, l.8 – 22va, l.14)&#xD;
III) Ṣalota ʿǝṭān "Prayer of the Incense" (fols. 22vb, l.1 – 53rb, l.13)&#xD;
IV) Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 53rb, l.14 – 91va, l.3)&#xD;
II-2) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 91ra, l.4 – 106vb, l.10)&#xD;
II-3) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 106vb, l.11 – 114vb, l.12)&#xD;
II-4) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 114vb, l.13 – 120ra, l.16)&#xD;
II-5) Anaphora of St Dioscorus (fols. 120rb, l.1 – 124ra, l.9; the ʾAnbǝro ʾǝd of this Anaphora is added after the colophon, s. Additio 1)&#xD;
&#xD;
Additio 1; colophon.</summary>
